  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The CFD solver exposes three tunable configuration parameters — base mesh element size, hemolysis stress-threshold, and turbulence model damping coefficient — whose values were selected during the validation campaign. ValidationResults report outcomes at the chosen settings; however, no configuration binding node is linked and the ContextOfUse does not constrain which parameter values must be used at deployment. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
